        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think this pattern (`_poll_exclude_pattern`) should be used only to filter out notifications to the server and not what will be watched. What will be watched is normally controlled by the language server's response (`DidChangeWatchedFilesRegistrationOptions.watchers[i].globPattern`).\r\nCurrently it used like that, except in the fallback `watchdirs()` function, where it also filters out what will be watched.\r\nHardcoding `node_modules` there skips notifications that some servers (e.g. `tsgo`) do expect to receive. Overwriting the hardocded value requires to monkey patch an internal module (and not easily per language client).\r\nThe `node_modules` directory is one example of directories with a deep structure, but similar directories exist in other ecosystems (even in the same, web dev, ecosystem).\r\nIf the language server should not be solely responsible for what will be watched for some reason, I think that should be configurable by the user, per client, and not hardcoded for every client.\r\n",
